{"id":33,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":33,"title":"Chapter 30: Alma Counsels His Sons","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 30"],["h1","Alma Counsels His Sons"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p3"},"Alma was unhappy because of how wicked the Nephites had become. He talked to each of his sons about living righteously."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/35.15-16"},"Alma 35:15–16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p5"},"Alma told Helaman, his oldest son, to trust in God. He told him about the angel God had sent to tell Alma to stop destroying the Church."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.3,6"},"Alma 36:3, 6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p7"},"For three days Alma had suffered because of his guilt. Then he remembered his father’s teachings about Jesus, and he knew his sins could be forgiven."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.16-17"},"Alma 36:16–17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p9"},"Alma prayed for forgiveness, and joy replaced the pain in his soul. He was forgiven because he had faith in Jesus Christ and had repented."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.18-20"},"Alma 36:18–20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p11"},"Since then Alma had taught others the gospel so they could feel the same joy he had felt. God had blessed Alma because of his trust in God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.24,27"},"Alma 36:24, 27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p13"},"Alma gave Helaman the sacred records and told him to continue writing the history of their people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.1-2"},"Alma 37:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p15"},"Alma told him that if he kept the commandments, God would bless him and help him protect the records."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.13,16"},"Alma 37:13, 16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p17"},"Alma also told Helaman to pray every morning and night and to talk with God about everything he was doing so God could help guide him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.36-37"},"Alma 37:36–37"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p19"},"Alma was happy with his son Shiblon, who had been a brave missionary to the Zoramites. Shiblon had remained faithful even when they had stoned him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/38.3-4"},"Alma 38:3–4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p21"},"Alma reminded Shiblon that the only way to be saved is through Jesus Christ. Alma then encouraged his son to continue teaching the gospel."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/38.9-10"},"Alma 38:9–10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p23"},"Alma’s son Corianton had not kept the commandments. He had not been a faithful missionary while teaching the Zoramites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/39.2-3"},"Alma 39:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p25"},"Because of what Corianton had done, the Zoramites would not believe Alma’s teachings."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/39.11"},"Alma 39:11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p27"},"Alma told Corianton that people cannot hide their sins from God and that Corianton needed to repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/39.8-9"},"Alma 39:8–9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p29"},"Alma taught his son that everyone will be resurrected but only the righteous will live with God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/40.9-10,25-26"},"Alma 40:9–10, 25–26"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p31"},"This life is the time for people to repent and serve God, Alma said."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/42.4"},"Alma 42:4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p33"},"Reminding Corianton that he had been called to be a missionary, Alma told him to return to the Zoramites and teach the people to repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/42.31"},"Alma 42:31"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_033_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p35"},"Alma and his sons continued teaching the gospel. They taught by the power of the priesthood."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-30-alma-counsels-his-sons.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/43.1-2"},"Alma 43:1–2"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
